##A nursing employee returns to work during a home quarantine in Beijing, prompting 66 people to be quarantined for medical reasons

In response to the problem of epidemic prevention and control during the rework period, Zhang Qiang, deputy director of the Office of the Community Prevention and Control Group of the Beijing Municipal Leading Group for Epidemic Prevention and control, and deputy director of the Municipal Party Committee's Organization Department, announced that special care would be given to seven groups of people.





In response to the problem of epidemic prevention and control during the rework period, Zhang Qiang, deputy director of the Office of the Community Prevention and Control Group of the Beijing Municipal Leading Group for Epidemic Prevention and control, and deputy director of the Municipal Party Committee's Organization Department, announced that special care would be given to seven groups of people.



A nursing employee returned to work during a home quarantine in Beijing, causing 66 people, including company colleagues, to be placed under medical quarantine.

The case was reported by Pang Xinghuo, deputy director of the COVID-19, at a press conference on the prevention and control of pneumonia in Beijing on February 21,2020.

It is reported that the case because of close contact with the confirmed case was isolated at home. He developed sore throat on February 13 while under observation at a home hospital, but it has not been reported. It was not until 18 February, when the symptoms worsened, that they were reported to the community staff and diagnosed as new crown pneumonia on 19 February.

According to Pang Xinghuo, because the case returned to work on February 10, the CDC conducted a screening of its workplace, and finally designated a total of 66 close contacts, all of whom were under centralized medical isolation, more than 200 other general contacts have been placed in home medical isolation.

Pang Xinghuo stressed that every enterprise must attach great importance to prevention and control work when resuming work, and should pay attention to the management of a large number of working teams and posts, to assess the route of workers to work, the density of people in the office, and the feasibility of decentralized work, and to develop flexible work systems and implement flexible work systems for possible risk points during the epidemic, in order to reduce the intensity of personnel, many forms and schemes, such as staggered rush hour and network work, are adopted.

"I want to tell you through this case, for the prevention and control of the epidemic do not take any chances, do not put prevention and control programs and plans on paper, documents. We should implement the prevention and control measures as well as resuming work and production, otherwise we will pay for it,"said Pang Xinghuo.

In response to online rumors of a cluster of infections at the People's Hospital of Peking University, Pang Xinghuo said at a news conference that so far, the Beijing Municipal Center for Disease Control and Prevention has not received any more reports from the People's Hospital of Peking University regarding newly confirmed cases or any samples that tested positive, "At present, the outpatient clinic and fever clinic of Peking University People's Hospital are still open and not closed. "

According to a recent report by the Beijing Center for Disease Control and Prevention, the People's Hospital of Peking University recently confirmed three cases of new coronary pneumonia. The People's Hospital of Peking University also vacated the Baita Monastery area for the observation of 142 patients with possible exposure to renal dialysis.

In addition, Zhang Qiang, deputy director of the Office of the Community Prevention and Control Group and Deputy Director of the Organization Department of the Municipal Party Committee, announced at a press conference that special care would be given to the seven categories of people.

The seven special groups are:

1. Persons who have not stayed in the territory of the People's Republic of China in the past 14 days and have entered the country through the ports of Capital International Airport and Beijing Daxing International Airport shall be exempted from the requirement of home observation for 14 days. Health Declaration card, Health Declaration, temperature test, face mask and distance should be kept.

2. Personnel who enter or return to Beijing from other areas within the territory of China (excluding Hubei Province) on a short-term basis (have no fixed residence or occupation in Beijing and are mainly engaged in tourism, visit, business, study tours, transit and other activities) shall cooperate with the management of their stay in hotels, when entering or leaving the hotel, you should take temperature, fill in the reason of coming to Beijing and register your contact person in Beijing. If there is a fever or physical discomfort, to timely medical treatment and take the initiative to inform the hotel and reception.

3. Personnel returning from other parts of China (excluding Hubei Province) to Beijing to resume work and resume work shall be under closed management if they meet the conditions for centralized work, and may work while observing on the premise of good protection; other personnel, or do you have to stay home for 14 days before you start.

4. Beijing staff who live in beijing-surrounding areas such as the north three counties of Langfang City in Hebei Province, and who commute to and from work as part of their daily routine, are not required to do so, but they are subject to routine inspection when entering and leaving Beijing.

5, Civil Aviation crew, railway crew members, these personnel frequent return to and from different places, is a rigid job demand, return to Beijing to live together.

6. For the need of unit management and Family Safety, the staff members of the central units in Beijing who travel to and from the areas with high incidence of the epidemic shall, upon their return to Beijing, be placed in isolation for office and residence in accordance with the regulations.

During the period of home observation, persons with special needs, such as pregnant women and those who are ill, may go out for medical examination according to the doctor's advice.
